content: Simply does not do what it claims. Tried it with several music pieces. Didn't accurately measure any of them.
A must have! Works amazingly well. Still the only app of its kind that will give you a graph. I'm a drummer, it helps to keep me honest about my time.
Seems to be the only app out there that can detect tempo.

Fantastic app! I tried several other BPM apps to automatically read out BPM's of my hip hop vinyl records and none of them worked - not even close. The only thing that worked was to manually "tap" an app to count BPM - that is certainly not something I want to do. liveBPM worked immediately and it's FAST. Within 4 bars of most vinyl I tested, it knew the BPM. Perfect for setting up my records before a set to put them in BPM order. Money well spent as it saves me tons of time.

This app is an excellent, must-have app for all musicians! Well worth the price. I've been using it for years at practice and at all gigs. The graph is a great feature. One request for additional capability is I'd like to be able to save the graphs. Sometimes I'm told my drumming was too fast/slow at certain parts and a saved graph could settle any arguments! One more thing- the developer is a fantastic, responsive person. I had an issue once and he replied immediately to help me. Great app!!

it says that it is for a previous version of android and needs to be updated... been using this for a while and i switched phones... this app needs to be updated for the newee version of android phones thanks
Great tool. Now I just need to get my drummer to use it!

Works with entire drum set, you start playing and it reads out the BPM after about four seconds then you just glance down at it once in a while to see how you're doing. This is a must have! Even recordes a graphical display,. The first time I tried it after about 5 minutes, I looked down and I was rushing about 6 BPM I couldn't believe it! I checked it against a metronome and it's spot-on. After about an hour I could stay within one BPM after 10 minutes playing. Easily worth 4 times the price

This app does not work on my phone for some reason but don't expect a refund if it doesn't work on yours because apparently this isn't thair policy if I could give it zero stars I would! A no refund policy says to me that they know how inferior the app is but don't care and just want your money!! This is theivary
replyContent: Well, in this case you need to write me an email. No reason to spam the review section.

content: I use it to sync my turntable speed to digital recordings 👌
Priceless tool for musicians!
Very useful for drumming practice. I put a metronome in ear phones and use this to see if I am matching it
Looks ok but it's out of date and is not working properly on my S9. Otherwise it looks like a good app for drummers.
I paid and downloaded this and I cant seem to find it

The five star rating is how well it worked with earlier Android versions. While it gives you a warning that it may not work with current Android releases, it is terrible now on my Google Pixel :-( hope it is upgraded soon!

Works great, I use it a lot while practicing with band and on gigs and it is much better than classic metronome. I play mostly jazz, I often slow down or speed up and this helps me a lot to maintain same tempo without having to have earphones with clicking metronome. Don't expect that it will show you actual tempo precisely, but the most powerful feature is the graph, where you can see your tempo trend right away with quick blink of your eye.
This app is not working on Samsung A30 android phone.Please return my money or else I will raise complaint in play store of cheating.
Awesome. Accurate. Easy.
I wish there were options for which mic to use, but I can't find any Regardless though, this app is really f****Ing awesome
Great to ensure correct pace without need for clicktrack

Not sure how well this works with other instruments but I'm a drummer and this is a fantastic tool to have. I often use it during live performances. I purchased a phone clamp that attaches to my high hat stand, where it's in easy view and out of the way. When you count off the beat to a song it registers the BPM within a just few seconds of playing and I'll just look at it every now and then to make sure my tempo hasn't fluctuated to much in real time. It really helps to keep you in the pocket.
Only good for drums. Didnt pick up my picking on my gtar.

Would be 5 stars but...after using it twice in a day it comes up a blank screen when trying to open the app. I even tried a force close. The only thing that fixes the issue is a restart of the device. I am an android user on the Samsung Galaxy S9 plus. This happened on my previous device as well.
doesnt detect below 72 bpm...so no more slow songs
Awesome app. Would be nice if you could enter a target bpm and have the color change if you're too fast or slow.
A bit too jumpy and laggy for me.
By far my favorite app in the world! It's flawless. I've tried all the free ones and they don't come close to this one!
The bpm number fluctuates on all tracks i used it on, and it never finalizes what the final bpm reading is.
I've looking for something like this for years! Great tool for drummers and bands. Throw away that metronome and sterile click tracks. Let's you play with feel!
Once you get used to the time-averaging you will find this app indispensable, especially on stage.
very accurate thumbs up
Love it! Tells you what you are doing without imposing the rigidity of a metronome.😀🥁
exactly what a drummer wants
Aleays reads between 98 and 128 bpm. no way to change its range of detection. no options at all. if u only work in 98 bpm to 128 bpm its a good app
great app, really helps show me when my timing creeps and correct it

This is a great app. I don't usually pay for apps but this is so worth it. Really helps me pull back and not freight train a song. Split screen would be quite helpful so I can have it next to the music instead of using 2 devices. Metronome? Maybe that defeats the purpose? Still, I would use it if it were there.
Excellent app. Very helpful in practice. Easy to use. Don't tend to use graph but very useful reference to bmp.
just what I wanted

This app works great. I was struggling with my tempo. I had no idea I was fluctuating up and down. This app tells me real-time what my bpm is. It saved my gig! Its well worth the money spent and I highly recommend it.

This works really well even with the inbuilt mic. Easily picked up the beat from an accordion/violin combo, in a venue with a fair amount of background noise. Now there'll be no arguments over dancing tempo...!

This app is tremendously useful both in a group rehearsal setting and for individual practice. I highly recommend this app if you need real time feedback about tempo maintenance without having to use the "tap" function on your metronome. Syncopated rhythms can throw the app off, but I find that it's mostly accurate.

I've used this now for a couple of years as I play drums.  Though my tempos are pretty consistent, the band I was with at the time needed me to be even more so.  Since using LiveBPM and it has changed my drumming life.  I have it installed on my android phone so it is with me all time; I never play a gig without it.  At first I wanted to look at it constantly, but now I just glance at it when I feel a change to check myself.  But it's not a metronome that you follow, it follows you.  So it has helped me by allowing me to feel my speeding up or slowing down and make the adjustment.  Kind of like letting me make the mistake and fix it instead of dictating what it wants me to do.  A must for any drummer since we are the keepers of the time!  BTW Daniel, how about versions for Windows and Linux?
I use this app for drum practice, very useful. I would love if it could be used in split screen mode or a floating window over other apps.
This was very accurate and able to handle all types of music I tested with. Definitely worth the buy!

when I first saw this app I pretty ecstatic, however as I used it my thoughts on it changed and now i'm like eh it's ok. this thing tends to have a slight delay on. Even with the few flaws it's still a pretty good thing to use as assistance.

Seems to work quite well. Didn't realize it was landscape orientation only. On gigs, I mount my tablet in landscape mode, but use my phone in portrait mode (for set lists). Please add portrait orientation option.
The interface could be reworked. An addition of delay times in ms would be great too. Never the less it is the best working app of its kind. Most bpm apps offer only tap tempo not recognition.
very useful
As a dj everything I play is by BPM. This app is rock solid and gives a graph of the speed of the music over time. Amazing app. Worth every penny
Works well
It's like an app version of the "beat bug"
It does exactly what it says on the tin. I find it incredibly useful to keep the tempo solid. Almost perfect app!

LiveBPM is stunningly accurate; it is great at what it does: Detect and display real-time tempos. It is a pleasure to use - a must-have app for any musician or band, and is worth far more than it costs!

It's not just that it does what it says perfectly - it's that it starts working immediately you start up the app without blundering through a menu or anything, perfect for a gig situation.  The display is large and easy to read from a distance, the buttons very clear - it's clearly been designed by people who have played live gigs!  The beat detection is excellent - it could pick up just my left hand on the piano. It's transformed the way I practise.  Those who complain that it doubles or halves the BPM - it just displays what it hears, what we feel as 180 might be recorded as 90 - if there's a prominent 1 and 3 it will hear that as the main beat.
Absolutely no instructions on how to use I don't get it

I have stubborn band mates that refuse to play to a click and this is an 
awesome compromise.

This app is invaluable to an acoustic band: it is trustworthy, it includes 
a graph so you can monitor tempo changes over a longer time, and it is 
clear and non confusing, all features that other bpm apps I've tried lack. 
I play in a live acoustic folk band for dancers. You may have to set your 
tempo range to the middle and multiply the displayed tempo by 2 for playing 
above 200bpm - this is easy to do, and many folk tempos are written like 
this to begin with. I have found that in my ensemble, I'm often presented 
with one of two values that are swapped between frequently when playing 
waltzes, which is unsurprising to me: it can't decide if its hearing beats 
1 2 3 or just 1, which it then doubles because its out of the tempo range. 
This also is not the app at fault, and manageable. A night mode with 
inverted colours would be appreciated.
The  app is amazing... Can you increase the max range to maybe 220?
Works very well.

Love the app. Very useful,  precise, helpful. But I need more options setting: Portrait and landscape, color options etc. Fonts, maybe a better interface. 4 stars from me. Thank you for this lovely and useful app.
Does not work above 200. Quickstep can be above 200.
Works great! As a drummer I wish it would have a click in function. Please add!!!
This is a great tool for individual & ensembles. I use it on my small gigs & use it on my HS marching percussion group.
I am unable to install on my Pixel with Android 8.0 (Oreo). It is stuck at 100%.
replyContent: This seems to be an issue unrelated to both Android 8.0 and our app. Depending on the case, restarting the phone, relogging into the Play Store, etc. may help?

content: Love it
worth - every - penny.

Best thing since sliced bread.  As a drummer, I sometimes get 'singers ' harping on about the song speeding up when it hasn't and it's all my fault because I. I'm supposed to keep time.  Well, this app solves it all guys. It really works. Happy or what!!
Brilliant for any drummer/ musician
Does not work with jazz drumming. Also seems to double the bpms at slow speeds.
Fantastic product. Intuitive user interface. Well-worth the price for a gigging drummer. Thank you Daniel!

I just started using the app and like it already. It will help me learn to keep steady when practicing my Hanon scales as well as the rest of my lessons. Sometimes the app halves or doubles the BPM depending on what it hears or how I play. This may end up helping me with dynamics. I used to wonder if an app like this existed. Glad I found this one.

Tried several free ones that weren't too bad but not really as accurate or reliable as I needed.  This one really found the tempo and held onto it.  The timeline feature is worth the cost alone.  I was able to play back some rough mixes and clearly see which ones had the better and the worse tempo variations.  Very pleased with this app,  I consider it the best of the bunch.
Cant get my refund back. It did not work very well.  Only just installed. Please refund.
replyContent: Please contact me via email. More information is needed to identify your purchase.

content: liveBRM
A must-have for drummers....

Brilliant piece of software. A really helpful tool for musicians. It helps me to see about where my BPM are in relation to my practice on a metronome. I also get to see how accurate other musicians are. ;-)  Seems fairly accurate.
Just Great for arriving at a songs tempo, works much better than others things I've tried..  Quicker too! Thank You for a Great app..
Great app, I have been using it for a while. But it stopped working since I updated my note 4 to Android 6. Please fix!!!!
replyContent: Android 6 has a new permission system. Please make sure, liveBPM has access to the microphone (see Android settings).

content: Update: I have been using this for more than 3 years now, at least 2x a week for live performances... Nothing on android compares in actually HEARING tempo. Still awesome after 3 years.
This app has helped me stay on target.
Musthave!

It does exactly what it tells : show you in real time the BPM it detect via the microphone. It's been years now that we use it with my rock band in rehearsal, on variety of devices, and it never failed.

It is good to practice with a metronome, but what do you do when you get out of sync? Here's the answer! This is a metronome that follows you instead of you following it. It's one of those rare tools that, one you've seen it, it's impossible to justify not working with it.

I tested this app by holding it right next to a digital metronome. It reported 80 BPM as 160 BPM and 200 BPM as 100 BPM. The app seems to double or halve the true BPM to normalize the result so that it falls within some expected range. That's not what I need the app to do, so I returned it for a refund.
I use this whenever I play a gig, and it helps me figure out where I'm rushing or dragging. It's also cool to turn it on and hide the screen and look at tempo fluctuations after each song.
It had one job. And it worked!
Its not accurate when I drum slow it detects 196 but when I drum fast I get ---.
Had some issues with it in the beginning.... but it was taken care of very quickly and efficiently... Get this app !
Just Buy It!!   For keeping track of your tempo during live gigs, set it up for the drummer to see..Bang on tempo, Speedy Detection, No "sensors".   Boom!
Use it all the time with the band!
I use it for drum and piano practice and it is on the money as far as live BPM detection!
Brilliant
Since sliced bread. This is what God loves. BRAVO!
Awsome ...app :-) Thanks  Dan !!!!!

I didn't think it would work after trying other apps but it does. Like magic. As a drummer i was worried about the high volumes but i had no issues with high sound levels at all.  by some weird voodoo it can even get the tempo on free form jazz. A must for any drummer. Brilliant!!!
Saved the day (night ) again. For got my phone at the gig Lucky was able to connect to wireless on my android tablet and download the app. Thanks Dan.
Really saves time when needing to find a tempo for a song. Worth the money.

This app is just amazing in its stability and the range of music for which it can track the beat.  (Obviously, just don't expect it to measure the beat of a single line of violin, as one reviewer thought it might!   It needs something with an actual beat to listen to :) )
Fantastic app only bpm meter with decimal places no roundup to nearest bpm
This listens and displays the tempo perfectly. Exactly what I was looking for.

Using this at dance, on the piano, it works very well.  Practicing fiddle at home, it is no good at extracting the beat from the melody.  It does work if I put it on the floor by my foot and I tap on a hard surface.  Perhaps I am using it incorrectly, but it is not as magical as I thought it would be.
Very useful app.
unbelievable quality and accuracy!
Great app for practice and worked very well after one gig. Hope to see some color themes down the road
Tap or 'listen'. Works with tricky beats and in noisy environments. Shows the bpm on a graph, taking the guesswork out of variable counts when tapping.
Simple and sound.
I have used this about five gigs now and have quit using my previous tempo meter.  I used both for a few gigs to test the accuracy.  Dead on.   Thanks!  Every drummer should use this.
This is usless for my needs as I am looking to sample music at between 25 an 59 bpm.  This starts at 60bpm.
I've seen this app help drummers realize their timing problem and help them correct it.
This app works perfectly. This is definitely the best BPM app on the market. Worth the $3.99 HTC Rezound.  Djkj
I love this app, it allows me to improve, visibly, in rehearsal. It is a better tool than a metronome for developing rhythmic accuracy.  Thanks Daniel, I love it!
It would be nice to have vertical time lines displayed, perhaps every 15 seconds or so, to refer back to.  Or user inserted marker points...
I was dubious that this would work, but in rehearsal last night it tracked our song speed fantastically!  Now just make it prettier please :-)
